    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adderly</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Layard</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thirty-five, Eutin
                                    Place,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 17, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Layard</hi>: I enclose a letter to the man
                            in the federal army of whom I spoke to you, which you were so good as to
                            say you would have forwarded.</p>
                <p>His parents are ready to give any sum up to £50 for his discharge, which
                            I will guarantee. The man received $300 on the 2d of March, 1864, as
                            half of his bounty-money, and $13 a month’s pay ever since.</p>
                <p>He enlisted for three years. His address is as on the enclosed
                            letter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. B. ADDERLY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>A. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Layard,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
